title: $A bounces on Chinese share market calm
text:
Wed, Jul 29, 2015, 7:28 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 2 hrs 32 mins $A bounces on Chinese share market calm AAP – 40 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar has risen, shrugging off turbulence in China's stock markets. 
At 0630 AEST on Wednesday, the currency was trading at 73.25 US cents, up from 73.15 cents on Tuesday. 
The Shanghai Composite closed down 1.7 per cent on Tuesday, after opening four per cent lower and following its 8.5 per cent plunge on Monday. 
CURRENCY SNAPSHOT AT 0630 AEST ON WEDNESDAY 
One Australian dollar buys: 
* 73.25 US cents, from 73.15 cents on Tuesday 
* 90.50 Japanese yen, from 90.40 yen 
* 66.24 euro cents, from 66.17 euro cents 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session)
